    "NonXMLResume": {
      "TextResume": "BINEET KAUR CHOPRA\r\nContact: +918861605898 (India) ;  Email: bineetchopra@gmail.com\r\n\r\n\r\nPROJECT MANAGER/SENIOR FUNCTIONAL CONSULTANT/\r\nSENIOR BUSINESS ANALYST - BANKING\r\nSeeking career enhancements across Risk Management/Retail & Corporate Banking/IT\r\n/Investment Banking/Equity Research/Treasury industry at senior level positions\r\n\r\nPROFILE\r\nâ€¢  Dynamic & technically competent professional with domain expertise as a Functional\r\nConsultant/Business Analyst in the Risk Management, Investment Banking, Retail Banking, Retail\r\nLending, Retail e-Banking and Multi - Channel Solutioning domains.\r\nâ€¢  Academically brilliant with a Post Graduate Diploma in Management, specialization in Finance\r\nand Marketing. Currently spearheading JP Morgan as an Associate in the Investment Banking\r\ndomain.\r\nâ€¢  Adept at providing expertise in preparing functional and system requirement specific documents\r\nfor enhancing the product.\r\nâ€¢  Analytical, logical & detail-oriented mind, with a strong knowledge-base & an exceptional\r\ndiagnostic & problem-solving ability in congruence with superb communication.\r\nâ€¢  Good interpersonal & leadership traits coupled with proven abilities to analyse, multi-task &\r\nadapt, handle tasks under high-pressure environment.\r\n\r\nSKILLS\r\n\r\nDomains\tInvestment Banking, Risk Management, Retail &\r\nCorporate Lending\r\nBusiness Analysis Skills\tRequirement gathering, gap analysis, business\r\nrequirement document, functional requirement\r\nspecification, As Is and To Be process modelling\r\nProgramming Languages\tC, C++, JAVA, Mainframe, VHDL, HTML\r\nProject Tools\tORCAD, AUTOCAD, SPSS, Microsoft Visio, MS Project, Pencil,\r\nRational Team Concert, HP Quality Center/ALM\r\nRegulatory Reporting Tools\tAxiom\r\nPackages\tMS Office\r\nOperating Systems\tWindows, Unix, DOS\r\nFile Version Maintenance Tools\tVisual Safe Source (VSS), Rational Requisite Pro\r\n\r\nCERTIFICATIONS\r\n\r\nFRM (Financial Risk Manager) Level I conducted by GARP\r\nNCFM - Financial Markets - Beginner's Module\r\nITIL 2011 Foundation Exam\r\n\r\n\r\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\r\n\r\n\r\n1.  JP Morgan, Bangalore\r\n\r\nFrom May 2016 till date\r\n\r\nAssociate - Risk and Finance Technology (Regulatory Reporting using Axiom)\r\n\r\nJob Responsibilities\r\nâ€¢   Requirement gathering and requirement analysis\r\nâ€¢   Authoring business requirement documents, functional requirement specification\r\ndocuments and system requirement specification documents\r\nâ€¢   Interaction with the business users, the technical team and the quality assurance team\r\nâ€¢   User Acceptance Testing\r\n\r\nProjects\r\nâ€¢   Internal Models Method for Credit Risk Measurement as per Basel III\r\nâ€¢   Internal Models Approach for Market Risk Measurement as per Basel III\r\nâ€¢   Shadow Banking\r\nâ€¢   Regulatory Reporting for Credit Risk, Market Risk and Liquidity Risk in Axiom as per\r\nBasel III\r\nâ€¢   Private Banking Customer Shortfall\r\nâ€¢   Private Banking Cash Collateral Netting\r\nâ€¢   EBA Pillar 3\r\nâ€¢   FINREP\r\n\r\n2.  Capco Technologies, Bangalore\r\n\r\nClient - Morgan Stanley\r\n\r\nFrom July 2014 till May, 2016\r\n\r\nProject Manager - Investment Banking - Securities Reference Data\r\n\r\nJob Responsibilities\r\nâ€¢   Project planning\r\nâ€¢   Requirement gathering and requirement analysis\r\nâ€¢   Authoring business requirement documents, functional requirement specification\r\ndocuments and system requirement specification documents\r\nâ€¢   Interaction with the business users, the technical team and the quality assurance team\r\nâ€¢   User Acceptance Testing\r\n\r\nProjects\r\n\r\nâ€¢   Reconciliation between Securities Reference Database and Vendor Systems\r\nâ€¢   Straight Through Processing of Corporate Actions\r\nâ€¢   Enhancements to Securities Reference Database\r\n\r\n\r\nConsultant - Investment Banking - Derivatives\r\n\r\nJob Responsibilities\r\nâ€¢   Requirement gathering and requirement analysis\r\nâ€¢   Authoring business requirement documents, functional requirement specification\r\ndocuments and system requirement specification documents\r\nâ€¢   Interaction with the business users, the technical team and the quality assurance team\r\nâ€¢   User Acceptance Testing\r\nâ€¢   Industry Testing with real counterparties/investment banks\r\nâ€¢   Mentoring and handholding new joinees\r\n\r\nProjects\r\nâ€¢   Equity Swaps on Markitwire\r\n(Markitwire is an electronic platform used for trade capture, legal confirmation and\r\nworkflow management across the industry)\r\nâ€¢   T0 Swaps Renovation\r\nâ€¢   Intellimatch Reconciliation of Equity Swaps and Equity Derivatives\r\nâ€¢   Straight through processing of Corporate Actions\r\n\r\n\r\n3.  Encora Technologies, Malaysia\r\n\r\nClient - CIMB Bank\r\n\r\nFrom April 2014 till June 2014\r\n\r\nSenior Business Analyst - Corporate Lending\r\n\r\nJob Responsibilities\r\nâ€¢   Requirement gathering and requirement analysis\r\nâ€¢   Authoring functional and system requirement specification documents\r\nâ€¢   Interaction with the business users\r\n\r\nProjects\r\nâ€¢   Straight Through Processing of Corporate Loan  Lifecycle (Origination, Servicing, Rollover,\r\nDelinquency Handling, Renewal, Cancellation) for CIMB Bank (Malaysia, Thailand,\r\nIndonesia, Singapore)\r\n\r\n4.  Societe Generale Global Solution Centre, Bangalore\r\n\r\nFrom May 2013 till April 2014\r\n\r\nBusiness Analyst - Investment Banking - Reference Data\r\n\r\nJob Responsibilities\r\nâ€¢   Working on Agile technology in a Scrum environment\r\nâ€¢   Requirement gathering and requirement analysis\r\nâ€¢   Authoring functional and system requirement specification documents\r\nâ€¢   Handling change requests\r\nâ€¢   Interaction with the clients and the technical team\r\n\r\nProjects\r\n\r\nâ€¢   Creation of Client Referential Data\r\na) Client Account Opening Workflow\r\nb) Client Modification Workflow\r\nc) Client Onboarding\r\nd) Legal & KYC Compliance\r\ne) Creation of Client Referential Data for Third Parties\r\nf) Creation of Elementary Clients and Legal Entities\r\ng) Legal & KYC Compliance\r\nh) Dodd Frank Act\r\ni) FATCA\r\nj) 15a6 rule\r\nk) SGAS\r\nl) E-Management of Operational Onboarding\r\n\r\n\r\n5.  ITC Infotech India Limited, Bangalore\r\n\r\nFrom April 2011 till April 2013\r\n\r\nLead Business Analyst - Risk Management\r\n\r\nJob Responsibilities\r\nâ€¢   Working on Agile technology in a Scrum environment\r\nâ€¢   Worked onsite at client location in Denmark\r\nâ€¢   Market study, current system study, gap analysis\r\nâ€¢   Analysis of roadmap items, feasibility analysis and preparation of proof of concept (POC)\r\nâ€¢   Requirement gathering and requirement analysis\r\nâ€¢   Authoring functional and system requirement specification documents\r\nâ€¢   Handling change requests\r\nâ€¢   Interaction with the clients and the technical team\r\nâ€¢   Handling internal supplier agreements with the data warehouse team\r\nâ€¢   Imparting domain related training and presentations to the technical team\r\nâ€¢   Training and handholding new team members\r\nâ€¢   Interviewing prospective candidates\r\n\r\n\r\nProjects\r\n\r\nâ€¢   Risk Management\r\na)  Basel Compliance\r\nb)  Credit risk - Standardized, Foundation IRB and Advanced IRB approaches\r\nc)  Probability of Default, Loss given default, Exposure at default and Maturity\r\nd)  Market risk - Standardized and Internal Models Approach\r\ne)  Operational risk - Basic Indicator, Standardized and Advanced Measurement\r\napproaches\r\nf)  Stress testing, backtesting\r\ng)  Automatic Limits (Pre-Approved Limits)\r\nh)  Shadow Limits\r\ni)  Portfolio Loan Concept\r\nj)  Facility Pricing Tool\r\nk)  Application Scoring\r\nl)  Behavioral Scoring\r\nm)  Credit Rating\r\nn)  Facility Pricing Tool\r\no)  Derivatives - Options, Futures, Forwards, Swaps, Credit Derivatives\r\n\r\nâ€¢   Retail Lending\r\na)  Interest Subsidy Loans\r\n\r\nâ€¢   Regulatory Compliance\r\na)  FATCA - Foreign Account Tax Compliance Act\r\n\r\nâ€¢   Multi-channel Solutioning\r\na)  Safe Deposit Box\r\nb)  Interactive Voice Response System\r\nc)  Net Budget (Personal Wealth Management Planner)\r\nd)  Teller System\r\ne)  Retail E-banking\r\n\r\nâ€¢   Training\r\na)  Underwent intensive training on Agile technology\r\n\r\n\r\n6.  Infosys Technologies Limited, Bangalore\r\n\r\nFrom May 2008 till April 2011\r\n\r\nSenior Associate Consultant - Finacle (Basel Compliance, Retail Assets, Mortgages, Securitization)\r\n\r\nâ€¢  Deputed to keep track of various developments in the banking and financial sector.\r\nâ€¢  Accountable for interacting with clients and the technical team to incorporate various regulatory\r\nrequirements in Finacle, the banking product of Infosys.\r\nâ€¢  Spearheading efforts across production support activities and liaising with the technical team for customized\r\ndevelopments; responsible for enhancements within the product.\r\nâ€¢  Preparing functional and system requirement specifications for various clients.\r\nâ€¢  Responsible for authoring the retail banking newsletter, Retail Tale.\r\nâ€¢  Writing articles for the retail banking portal, Retail Bank Quest.\r\nâ€¢  Successfully completed functional and technical certifications in e-banking, Oracle, Unix and Retail\r\nConsumer Lending\r\nâ€¢  Delivered a presentation on Green IT.\r\nâ€¢  Entrusted with the task of keeping track of TCS as a competitor, in the core banking domain, SAP as a\r\ncompetitor, in the microfinance domain and Oracle as a competitor, in the Basel II domain.\r\nOn the Job Training:\r\nâ€¢  Underwent an intensive training in Finacle for one month\r\nâ€¢  Performed testing of fixed tickets, detected bugs and raised new tickets\r\n\r\nAuthored requirement specifications for the following enhancements in Finacle:\r\n\r\nâ€¢  Basel II data capture for making Finacle Basel compliant\r\nâ€¢  Credit risk - Standardized, Foundation IRB and Advanced IRB approaches\r\nâ€¢  Market risk - Standardized and Internal Models Approach\r\nâ€¢  VaR calculation - Historical, Variance - Covariance and Monte Carlo Simulation\r\nâ€¢  Operational risk - Basic Indicator, Standardized and Advanced Measurement approaches\r\nâ€¢  Stress testing, backtesting\r\nâ€¢  Reverse Mortgage Origination and Servicing\r\nâ€¢  Line of Credit (HELOC, PLOC, RELOC) Origination and Servicing for US and Canada markets\r\nâ€¢  Investor Reporting\r\nâ€¢  Escrow origination and servicing\r\nâ€¢  Rate Lock\r\nâ€¢  FASB 91\r\nâ€¢  Collateral revaluation and maintenance of collateral history\r\nâ€¢  Generation  of  a  quote/key  facts  illustration  from  the  Loan  Origination  System  and  the  Loan  Maintenance\r\nSystem\r\nâ€¢  Integration of Finanz Tools with the Loan Origination System in CRM\r\nâ€¢  Dormancy Status for Non-Financial Transactions\r\nâ€¢  Changing the behaviour of the menu option, HLACAM, which performs the amortization batch job\r\nâ€¢  Validation at the time of rephasement, keeping the EMI fixed and changing the tenor\r\nâ€¢  Carryover of charge demands\r\nâ€¢  Overflow carryover\r\nâ€¢  EMI plus interest on holiday period to be raised as a combined demand at the time of the first instalment\r\nâ€¢  Enabling  scheduled  and  unscheduled  loan  repayments  and  loan  disbursement  for  forward  contract\r\nutilization\r\nâ€¢  Accepting cheque for scheduled and unscheduled loan repayment and loan payoff\r\nâ€¢  Dropping of multiple disbursement parameter\r\nâ€¢  Securitization: Pool creation criteria based on geographic location of the mortgaged property\r\nâ€¢  Handling of minor's accounts\r\nâ€¢  Display of the portion of permitted annual overpayment used in a calendar year\r\nâ€¢  Analysis of cross-functional dependency of retail loans module on payment systems\r\nâ€¢  Calculation and display of Annual Percentage Rate (APR) as per CCA guideline for UK market\r\nâ€¢  Calculation and display of APR for loans having a subsidy amount\r\nâ€¢  Minimum balance check for automatic debits\r\n\r\nPROJECT\r\n\r\nPrice Waterhouse Coopers, New York - Onsite project for US market study, gap analysis, business\r\nrequirement gathering and developing functional requirement specifications\r\n\r\nAuthored the following requirement specifications for enhancements in Finacle:\r\n\r\nâ€¢  Mortgage (including Buydown) Origination and Servicing\r\nâ€¢  Investor Reporting\r\nâ€¢  Special Products- Adjustable Rate Mortgages (ARMs), Construction loans, Balloon loans\r\nâ€¢  Escrow Servicing for Mortgages and Liability accounts\r\nâ€¢  Impound Accounts, Buydowns and Buyups\r\nâ€¢  Liability (DDA accounts) Origination and Servicing\r\nâ€¢  Line Of Credit Origination (HELOC, PLOC, RELOC) and Servicing\r\nâ€¢  Personal Line of Credit Origination and Servicing\r\nâ€¢  Origination and Servicing of Boat Loans, Personal Loans and Auto Loans\r\nâ€¢  General Ledger\r\nâ€¢  Basel II Data Capture\r\nâ€¢  Minor Accounts\r\n\r\nWHITE PAPER\r\n\r\nâ€¢   Authored a white paper on \"Credit Ratings-Empty Rituals\"\r\n\r\nPROFESSIONAL ACHIEVEMENTS\r\nâ€¢   Awarded \"Gem of the Quarter Award\" for excellent contribution in Line of Credit enhancement\r\nâ€¢   Awarded \"On the Spot Award\" for contribution in Basel implementation\r\n\r\n\r\nEDUCATIONAL AND PROFESSIONAL QUALIFICATIONS\r\n\r\nPost Graduate Diploma in Management, Finance and Marketing - 2008\r\nSDM-IMD, Mysore, CGPA=3.25/4\r\n\r\nBachelor of Technology, Electronics and Communication Engineering - 2006\r\nGuru Tegh Bahadur Institute of Technology, New Delhi, 67.5%\r\n\r\n12th, 2002\r\nD.L.D.A.V. Model School, New Delhi, 68.6%\r\n\r\n10th, 2000\r\nMata Jai Kaur Public School, New Delhi, 83%\r\n\r\nScholastic Achievements\r\nâ€¢  Common Admission Test 2005: 84.31% percentile\r\nâ€¢  National Level Science Talent Search Examination scholarship holder\r\nâ€¢  Topped All India School Scholarship examination\r\nâ€¢  Won prizes in many Mathematics Olympiads\r\nâ€¢  Stood amongst the top 5\" students (out of 120 students) of the PGDM Batch 2006-2008 by securing a CGPA of\r\n3.25 on a scale of 4.0\r\n\r\nPapers Presented:\r\nâ€¢  Presented a research paper on India's Growth Story in Narsee Monjee Institute of Management\r\nâ€¢  Prepared a dissertation on Lessons from Sub-Prime Meltdown to CRISIL\r\nâ€¢  Participated in Cognizant Smart Business Plan 2007 Contest\r\n\r\nInternship\r\n\r\nOrganisation: Reliance Mutual Fund\r\nDuration: April-May 2007\r\nAim: Quantitative Analysis and Distribution Channel Management of Mutual Funds\r\nSynopsis:\r\nâ€¢   Prepared a project covering all the fundamental aspects relating to investment in mutual funds\r\nâ€¢   Built and strengthened relationships with distributors and helped to tackle the problems faced by\r\nthem\r\nâ€¢   Analyzed various funds and measured their risk by computing beta, Sharpe ratio and Treynor\r\nratio\r\n\r\nProjects:\r\nâ€¢  Presented a Seminar on Reverse Mortgage: An Option for Senior Citizens\r\n\r\n\r\nEXTRA CURRICULAR ACTIVITIES\r\n\r\nâ€¢  Was a part of the hospitality team in Pratigam '06 and '07, the Alumni Meet held at SDM-IMD,\r\nMysore.\r\nâ€¢  Actively contributed to the success of NAISSANCE '07 and '08, the management festival held at\r\nSDM-IMD, Mysore.\r\nâ€¢  Was the member of the winning team in the Britannia Heritage Quiz\r\nâ€¢  Participated in TCS Smart Manager Case Contest\r\nâ€¢  Took part in 4D Rule, the advertising event at Abhyudaya'08, IFMR.\r\nâ€¢  Was the student editor of the school magazine - Jaikaurites\r\n\r\nPermanent Address: Pocket A-1, Flat No. 20, Sector-5, Rohini, Delhi - 110085\r\nReferences: Available on Request"
